== Events == * {{ill|Tianzhi Tennō|ja|天智天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[667]] {{ill|April 17|ja|4月17日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Prince Nakano-Ōe (later known as {{ill|Tianzhi Tennō|ja|天智天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) relocated the capital to Ōmi and Ōtsu-kyō. * {{ill|Sūtei|ja|崇禎|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year / {{ill|Shunji|ja|順治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1644]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Rebel leader {{ill|Li Zicheng|ja|李自成|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} led his forces to occupy Beijing; Emperor {{ill|Chongzhen|ja|崇禎帝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} committed suicide, marking the collapse of the Ming dynasty. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1870]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – To oversee railway construction, the Japanese government established the Railway Section within the Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Ministry of Finance.
== Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1838]] {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Gotō Shōjirō|ja|後藤象二郎|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a politician and prominent figure in the Freedom and People's Rights Movement (died [[1897]]).
== Deaths == * [[Huangchu]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[223]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Cao Ren|ja|曹仁|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander from the Three Kingdoms period (born [[168]]). * [[Chiku]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[245]] {{ill|May 2|ja|5月2日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Lu Xun|ja|陸遜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and statesman (born [[183]]).
