* {{ill|Sūtei|ja|崇禎}} 17th year / {{ill|Shunji|ja|順治}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1644]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日}}) – Rebel leader {{ill|Li Zicheng|ja|李自成}} led his forces to occupy Beijing; Emperor {{ill|Chongzhen|ja|崇禎帝}} committed suicide, marking the collapse of the Ming dynasty.
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1870]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日}}) – To oversee railway construction, the Japanese government established the Railway Section within the Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Ministry of Finance.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1838]] {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日}}) – {{ill|Gotō Shōjirō|ja|後藤象二郎}}, a politician and prominent figure in the Freedom and People's Rights Movement (died [[1897]]).

== Deaths ==
* [[Huangchu]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[223]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日}}) – {{ill|Cao Ren|ja|曹仁}}, a military commander from the Three Kingdoms period (born [[168]]).
* [[Chiku]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[245]] {{ill|May 2|ja|5月2日}}) – {{ill|Lu Xun|ja|陸遜}}, a military commander and statesman (born [[183]]).


