'''March 19''' is the 19th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Tianzhi Tennō|ja|天智天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[667]] {{ill|April 17|ja|4月17日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Prince Nakano-Ōe (later known as {{ill|Tianzhi Tennō|ja|天智天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) relocated the capital to Ōmi and Ōtsu-kyō.
* {{ill|Sūtei|ja|崇禎|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year / {{ill|Shunji|ja|順治|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1644]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Rebel leader {{ill|Li Zicheng|ja|李自成|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} led his forces to occupy Beijing; Emperor {{ill|Chongzhen|ja|崇禎帝|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} committed suicide, marking the collapse of the Ming dynasty.
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1870]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – To oversee railway construction, the Japanese government established the Railway Section within the Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Ministry of Finance.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1838]] {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Gotō Shōjirō|ja|後藤象二郎|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a politician and prominent figure in the Freedom and People's Rights Movement (died [[1897]]).

== Deaths ==
* [[Huangchu]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[223]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Cao Ren|ja|曹仁|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander from the Three Kingdoms period (born [[168]]).
* [[Chiku]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[245]] {{ill|May 2|ja|5月2日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Lu Xun|ja|陸遜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and statesman (born [[183]]).


