{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 19일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 19''' is the 19th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Tianzhi Tennō|ja|天智天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[667]] {{ill|April 17|ja|4月17日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – Prince Nakano-Ōe (later known as {{ill|Tianzhi Tennō|ja|天智天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) relocated the capital to Ōmi and Ōtsu-kyō. * {{ill|Sūtei|ja|崇禎|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 17th year / {{ill|Shunji|ja|順治|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1644]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – Rebel leader {{ill|Li Zicheng|ja|李自成|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} led his forces to occupy Beijing; Emperor {{ill|Chongzhen|ja|崇禎帝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} committed suicide, marking the collapse of the Ming dynasty. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1870]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – To oversee railway construction, the Japanese government established the Railway Section within the Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Ministry of Finance.
== Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1838]] {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Gotō Shōjirō|ja|後藤象二郎|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a politician and prominent figure in the Freedom and People's Rights Movement (died [[1897]]).
== Deaths == * [[Huangchu]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[223]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Cao Ren|ja|曹仁|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a military commander from the Three Kingdoms period (born [[168]]). * [[Chiku]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[245]] {{ill|May 2|ja|5月2日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Lu Xun|ja|陸遜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a military commander and statesman (born [[183]]).
