== Events == * [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Tianzhi Tennō]] 6th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[667]] [[:en:April 17|April 17]]) – Prince Nakano-Ōe (later known as [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Tianzhi Tennō]]) relocated the capital to Ōmi and Ōtsu-kyō. * {{ill|Sūtei|ja|崇禎|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sūtei|qq=}} 17th year / {{ill|Shunji|ja|順治|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shunji|qq=}} 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1644]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – Rebel leader [[:en:Li Zicheng|Li Zicheng]] led his forces to occupy Beijing; Emperor [[:en:Chongzhen Emperor|Chongzhen]] committed suicide, marking the collapse of the Ming dynasty. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1870]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – To oversee railway construction, the Japanese government established the Railway Section within the Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Ministry of Finance.
== Births == * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1838]] [[:en:April 13|April 13]]) – [[:en:Gotō Shōjirō|Gotō Shōjirō]], a politician and prominent figure in the Freedom and People's Rights Movement (died [[1897]]).
== Deaths == * [[Huangchu]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[223]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – [[:en:Cao Ren|Cao Ren]], a military commander from the Three Kingdoms period (born [[168]]). * [[Chiku]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[245]] [[:en:May 2|May 2]]) – [[:en:Lu Xun (Eastern Wu)|Lu Xun]], a military commander and statesman (born [[183]]).
