{{Not to be confused with|March 19|qq=March 19}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 19일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 19''' is the 19th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Tianzhi Tennō]] 6th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[667]] [[:en:April 17|April 17]]) – Prince Nakano-Ōe (later known as [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Tianzhi Tennō]]) relocated the capital to Ōmi and Ōtsu-kyō. * {{ill|Sūtei|ja|崇禎|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sūtei|qq=}} 17th year / {{ill|Shunji|ja|順治|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shunji|qq=}} 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1644|1644]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – Rebel leader [[:en:Li Zicheng|Li Zicheng]] led his forces to occupy Beijing; Emperor [[:en:Chongzhen Emperor|Chongzhen]] committed suicide, marking the collapse of the Ming dynasty. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1870]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – To oversee railway construction, the Japanese government established the Railway Section within the Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Ministry of Finance.
== Births == * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1838|1838]] [[:en:April 13|April 13]]) – [[:en:Gotō Shōjirō|Gotō Shōjirō]], a politician and prominent figure in the Freedom and People's Rights Movement (died [[1897]]).
== Deaths == * [[Huangchu]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[223]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – [[:en:Cao Ren|Cao Ren]], a military commander from the Three Kingdoms period (born [[:en:168|168]]). * [[Chiku]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[245]] [[:en:May 2|May 2]]) – [[:en:Lu Xun (Eastern Wu)|Lu Xun]], a military commander and statesman (born [[:en:183|183]]).
