'''March 19''' is the 19th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|qid=Q96759842|1=senpu}}{{efn|ja|先負|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Emperor Tenji|en|Emperor Tenji|qid=Q314802|lt=Tianzhi Tennō|1=Emperor Tenji}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|667|en|667|qid=Q30702|lt=667|1=667}} {{ill|April 17|en|April 17|qid=Q2520|lt=April 17|1=April 17}}) – Prince Nakano-Ōe (later known as {{ill|Emperor Tenji|en|Emperor Tenji|qid=Q314802|lt=Tianzhi Tennō|1=Emperor Tenji}}) relocated the capital to Ōmi and Ōtsu-kyō.
* {{ill|Sūtei|ja|崇禎|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sūtei|1=Chongzhen Era|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q833637}} 17th year / {{ill|Shunji|ja|順治|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shunji|1=Shunzhi Era|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q1077244}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1644|en|1644|qid=Q6920|lt=1644|1=1644}} {{ill|April 25|en|April 25|qid=Q2531|lt=April 25|1=April 25}}) – Rebel leader {{ill|Li Zicheng|en|Li Zicheng|qid=Q333567|lt=Li Zicheng|1=Li Zicheng}} led his forces to occupy Beijing; Emperor {{ill|Chongzhen Emperor|en|Chongzhen Emperor|qid=Q10069|lt=Chongzhen|1=Chongzhen Emperor}} committed suicide, marking the collapse of the Ming dynasty.
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1870|en|1870|qid=Q7741|lt=1870|1=1870}} {{ill|April 19|en|April 19|qid=Q2523|lt=April 19|1=April 19}}) – To oversee railway construction, the Japanese government established the Railway Section within the Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Ministry of Finance.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1838|en|1838|qid=Q7612|lt=1838|1=1838}} {{ill|April 13|en|April 13|qid=Q2498|lt=April 13|1=April 13}}) – {{ill|Gotō Shōjirō|en|Gotō Shōjirō|qid=Q711721|lt=Gotō Shōjirō|1=Gotō Shōjirō}}, a politician and prominent figure in the Freedom and People's Rights Movement (died {{ill|1897|en|1897|qid=Q7847|lt=1897|1=1897}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Huangchu|en|Huangchu|qid=Q45313168|lt=Huangchu|1=Huangchu}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|223|en|223|qid=Q31243|lt=223|1=223}} {{ill|May 6|en|May 6|qid=Q2552|lt=May 6|1=May 6}}) – {{ill|Cao Ren|en|Cao Ren|qid=Q378439|lt=Cao Ren|1=Cao Ren}}, a military commander from the Three Kingdoms period (born {{ill|168|en|168|qid=Q24916|lt=168|1=168}}).
* [[:en:Chiku|Chiku]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|245|en|245|qid=Q32308|lt=245|1=245}} {{ill|May 2|en|May 2|qid=Q2545|lt=May 2|1=May 2}}) – {{ill|Lu Xun (Eastern Wu)|en|Lu Xun (Eastern Wu)|qid=Q378492|lt=Lu Xun|1=Lu Xun (Eastern Wu)}}, a military commander and statesman (born {{ill|183|en|183|qid=Q31386|lt=183|1=183}}).

